.TH "pci_p2pdma_add_resource" 9 "pci_p2pdma_add_resource" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_p2pdma_add_resource \- add memory for use as p2p memory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_p2pdma_add_resource
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "int bar "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "u64 offset "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
the device to add the memory to
.IP "bar" 12
PCI BAR to add
.IP "size" 12
size of the memory to add, may be zero to use the whole BAR
.IP "offset" 12
offset into the PCI BAR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The memory will be given ZONE_DEVICE struct pages so that it may
be used with any DMA request.
